---
layout: base
title: "Topics & Feeds"
description: "Browse all topics. Every tag has its own archive page and RSS feed. Subscribe to as many as you like."
permalink: /tags/
---

<div class="site-hero">
  <h1>Topics &amp; <em>feeds</em></h1>
  <p>Every topic has its own page and RSS feed. Subscribe to individual topics in your RSS reader, or import all of them at once.</p>
</div>

<div class="rss-explainer">
  <div class="rss-explainer__inner">
    <span class="rss-explainer__label">How to subscribe</span>
    <p>Click any <strong>Subscribe</strong> link to open the feed directly, then paste the URL into your RSS reader (Reeder, NetNewsWire, Feedly, etc.). Or download the <a href="/feeds/opml.xml" class="rss-explainer__opml">OPML bundle</a> to import all feeds at once.</p>
    <div class="rss-explainer__feeds">
      <a href="/feed.xml" class="rss-feed-link">
        <span class="rss-feed-link__label">All posts</span>
        <span class="rss-feed-link__url">/feed.xml</span>
        <span class="rss-feed-link__cta">Subscribe →</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/feeds/opml.xml" class="rss-feed-link rss-feed-link--opml">
        <span class="rss-feed-link__label">All feeds (OPML bundle)</span>
        <span class="rss-feed-link__url">/feeds/opml.xml</span>
        <span class="rss-feed-link__cta">Import →</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="tags-subscribe">
  {% for tag in collections.tagList %}
  {% set count = collections.posts | byTag(tag) | length %}
  <div class="tags-subscribe__item">
    <div class="tags-subscribe__info">
      <a class="tags-subscribe__name" href="/tag/{{ tag }}/">{{ tag }}</a>
      <span class="tags-subscribe__count">{{ count }} post{% if count != 1 %}s{% endif %}</span>
    </div>
    <a class="rss-feed-link rss-feed-link--compact" href="/feeds/tags/{{ tag }}/feed.xml">
      <span class="rss-feed-link__label">{{ tag }}</span>
      <span class="rss-feed-link__url">/feeds/tags/{{ tag }}/feed.xml</span>
      <span class="rss-feed-link__cta">Subscribe →</span>
    </a>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
